metatags.twitter:title: What is REAL ID?
metatags.og:title: What is REAL ID?
metatags.og:description: Effective May 7, 2025, a REAL ID Driver License or Non-Driver Identification Card, or a Passport is required to board an airplane for domestic flights or enter a secure federal facility.  REAL ID Driver Licenses or Non-Driver Identification Cards are marked with a star in the top right corner to indicate it may be used for federal identification. For more information, please visit our Real ID page.

metatags.twitter:title: Some New Hampshire DMV Branches To Open This Saturday For REAL ID Transactions
metatags.og:title: Some New Hampshire DMV Branches To Open This Saturday For REAL ID Transactions
metatags.og:description: CONCORD, N.H. – The New Hampshire Division of Motor Vehicles (DMV) announces multiple branches will open this weekend to accommodate demands for REAL ID-compliant driver’s licenses and non-driver identification cards. On Saturday, May 3, 2025, DMV branches in Concord, Manchester and Twin Mountain will offer appointments and walk-in services from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. Transactions will be limited to REAL ID services only. Appointments can be made online now through the DMV’s website.
